# Routing

Hono's router is one of the fastest in the JavaScript ecosystem.

## Basic Routing

```ts
const app = new Hono()

app.get('/', (c) => c.text('Hello!'))
app.post('/posts', (c) => c.json({ ok: true }))
app.put('/posts/:id', (c) => {
  const id = c.req.param('id')
  return c.json({ id })
})
```

## Route Parameters

You can use `:param` syntax for dynamic segments:

```ts
app.get('/users/:id', (c) => {
  const id = c.req.param('id')
  return c.json({ id })
})
```

## Wildcards

```ts
app.get('/posts/*', (c) => {
  return c.text('Wildcard matched')
})
```

# Context

The Context object `c` is passed to every handler and middleware.

## Request

```ts
app.get('/api/data', (c) => {
  const query = c.req.query('q')
  const header = c.req.header('Authorization')
  return c.json({ query, header })
})
```

## Response helpers

- `c.text(text)` - Plain text
- `c.json(data)` - JSON response
- `c.html(html)` - HTML response
- `c.redirect(url)` - Redirect
